\subsection*{Observed Physical Quantities}
\begin{frame}
\frametitle{Observed Physical Quantities}
observational apperance of a ns is affected by the redshifeted and lensed effects when propagating
\item in the scwarzschild metric, $$g_{tt} = - 1(1 - 2GM/Rc^2)$$
the gravitational eefects on the observational apperance of a slowly spinning ns can be caracterized by a single paramer, compactness, $p = 2GM/Rc^2$
\item the redshif tis $1+z = |g_{tt}|^{-1/2}$
\item the len from the strong grav field gives an area to apperar large by an area of $$S_{\infty}/4\pi R^2 = (1+z)^2$$
\iten $T_{eff, \infty} = T_{eff,s}/1+z$
\item the total flux observed from the ns at D is $$F_{\infty} = \sigma_B T^4_{eff,\infty} \Big ( |frac{R}{D} \Big)^2 (1+z)^2$$
\item the eddigton lum at inf is
$$L_{E,\inft} = \frac{8\pi m_pc}{(1+X)\sigma_T} \Big (1 - \frac{2GM}{Rc^2} \Big)^{1/2}$$
\end{frame}



